		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sun, Jan 30th 8:17 PM2005 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=14&mid=110713433427760303&post=1"><a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=14&mid=110713433427760303&num=6&post=1&replyto=110713433427760303"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=110713433427760303></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=486121"><span id=>Risingmyst</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br />20 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Risingmyst&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>My Necro Risingmyst is on the Prexus Sever and is nearly LvL 51.<br>Thus far I've acted as a healing Necro in groups. Also I'v been playing the role of mana battery via the Twiching spells. An Rl friend and I have had disputes on what Necro's can and should do. He plays endgame lvl. I do not. Anyway, he says necros can never heal in groups and should only twich. I think he's thinking from an endgame point of view. Would not know about that Til my Necro attains that lvl range. I play a devious an inventive Necro. How I play depends much on the situation encountered. When grouped with a single warrior I can easily keep one healed provided we time pulls. I began doing this in overthere in my 30's. In Dulak a group of people tried to steal a camp spot ( one of the boats) but they did not have a healer. At the time I was grouped with a Bst Lord, my heals made a huge difference in that situation. The individuals died there. And I made no effort to help them. I detest and despise KSers. Anyway it was my abiltiy to heal that kept us in our camp area. In Ldons I've been very effective in supplementing a Clerics heals. And when no Cleric or other healer was present I was able to fill this role and still had mana to spare for twiching other casters on a timed basis. I've experiemented with our version of devine aura. Once a chanter in a group I was with was about to dy in Rath, a gaint he had charmed decided to rebel and attacked the Chanter. I did not feel I had time for casting before He died. So, being near I moved my mount infront of it, got agro and then cast the devine aura equivalent. (can't recall spell name off hand). I often use it in this fashion. And the giants..lol..turned out there was a second I did not see were pounding away at me as I just sat there. I typed shielding Chanter from harm as the mobs were so engaged. The party was then able to deal with these giants and I backed off as the warriors gained the agro and began healing then in turn as they were low on hp from their previous targets. As I said I play inventively or try to. Was just wondering what tricks or suggestions any of you have. Further any advice for playing style for lvls higher than lvl 51 would be appreciated. I feel playing one's character properly is using whatever abilties one has to aide ones group or self furtherment regardless of percieved traditiional roles..i.e. I firmly believe in being inventive...lol<br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >6 Replies</td></tr></table>
